# Technical Article Publication Checklist

## Content Structure
- [ ] Clear introduction with problem statement
- [ ] Logical flow of concepts
- [ ] Proper heading hierarchy (h1 → h2 → h3)
- [ ] Consistent terminology throughout
- [ ] Strong conclusion with next steps

## Technical Quality
- [ ] Code examples tested and verified
- [ ] Technical accuracy reviewed
- [ ] Performance implications discussed
- [ ] Security considerations addressed
- [ ] Browser/environment compatibility noted
- [ ] Dependencies and versions specified
- [ ] Error handling demonstrated

## Code Examples
- [ ] Syntax highlighting used
- [ ] Error handling included
- [ ] Comments explain complex parts
- [ ] Consistent formatting
- [ ] Complete and self-contained
- [ ] Security best practices followed
- [ ] Performance considerations noted

## Diagrams and Visuals
- [ ] Technical diagrams included where helpful
- [ ] Alt text provided for all images
- [ ] Dark/light mode support
- [ ] Responsive scaling tested
- [ ] Source files included
- [ ] Consistent style with guidelines

## Accessibility
- [ ] Proper heading structure
- [ ] Alt text for all images
- [ ] Sufficient color contrast
- [ ] No reliance on color alone
- [ ] Code blocks properly marked
- [ ] Links have descriptive text
- [ ] Tables have proper headers

## SEO and Metadata
- [ ] Title is descriptive and unique
- [ ] Description is compelling (150-160 chars)
- [ ] Keywords naturally incorporated
- [ ] Tags are relevant and consistent
- [ ] Series links correct (if applicable)
- [ ] Canonical URL set correctly
- [ ] Social media preview tested

## Frontmatter Example
```yaml
---
title: 'Understanding Feature Flags: A Comprehensive Guide'
description: 'Learn how to implement feature flags in your applications with real-world examples and best practices for scalable solutions.'
date: 2024-02-17
authors: ['username']
tags: ['feature-flags', 'architecture', 'best-practices']
series: 'feature-flags'
seriesOrder: 1
draft: false
---
```

## Links and References
- [ ] Internal links work correctly
- [ ] External links open in new tabs
- [ ] Reference links are valid
- [ ] Series navigation correct
- [ ] Author links accurate
- [ ] Related articles linked

## Writing Quality
- [ ] Spelling and grammar checked
- [ ] Technical terms explained
- [ ] Consistent voice and tone
- [ ] No unexplained acronyms
- [ ] Clear and concise writing
- [ ] Professional language used

## Reader Experience
- [ ] Prerequisites clearly stated
- [ ] Learning objectives defined
- [ ] Progressive complexity
- [ ] Examples build on each other
- [ ] Key takeaways summarized
- [ ] Next steps provided

## Performance
- [ ] Images optimized
- [ ] Code blocks not too long
- [ ] No unnecessary imports
- [ ] Lazy loading used where appropriate
- [ ] Resource sizes reasonable
- [ ] Page load time tested

## Final Review
- [ ] Technical review completed
- [ ] Editorial review completed
- [ ] Author bio updated
- [ ] Social sharing tested
- [ ] Mobile rendering checked
- [ ] Print layout verified
- [ ] RSS feed validated

Remember:
- Quality over quantity
- Technical accuracy is paramount
- Reader experience is crucial
- Accessibility cannot be an afterthought
- SEO should feel natural, not forced 